<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="310" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[113,1095,343,814]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,343,366]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ZAYAS F." box="[231,373,343,366]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" refId="ref52425" refString="ZAYAS F. 1989: Entomofauna Cubana. Orden Coleoptera. Separata descripcion de nuevas especies. Editorial Cientifico-Tecnica, La Habana, 212 pp." type="book" year="1989">ZAYAS (1989)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on series of 
<specimenCount box="[820,966,343,366]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" type="generic">17 specimens</specimenCount>
and placed it in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spaeth, 1899" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[268,580,375,398]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,435,375,398]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SPAETH F." box="[441,580,375,398]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" pagination="213 - 221" refId="ref50724" refString="SPAETH F. 1899: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen III. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 49: 213 - 221 + pl. 5." type="journal article" year="1899">Spaeth, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
without any additional comment supporting the placement. He also provided a figure, which does not look like any of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[921,1088,407,430]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The collection of Zayas is in possession of his family and is currently inaccessible. Mike Ivie (Bozman, 
<collectingRegion box="[332,430,471,494]" country="United States of America" name="Montana" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Montana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[440,495,471,494]" name="United States of America" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">USA</collectingCountry>
) was able to examine the collection and kindly provided a photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[339,432,503,526]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zayas" authorityYear="1989" box="[473,615,503,526]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tortuguilla">
<emphasis box="[473,615,503,526]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">P. tortuguilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the photograph and the primary description I hereby transfer the species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[680,767,535,558]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Asteriza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,767,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Asteriza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[113,1095,343,814]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">
<bibRefCitation author="ZAYAS F." box="[144,289,567,590]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" refId="ref52425" refString="ZAYAS F. 1989: Entomofauna Cubana. Orden Coleoptera. Separata descripcion de nuevas especies. Editorial Cientifico-Tecnica, La Habana, 212 pp." type="book" year="1989">ZAYAS (1989)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authority="Bon" authorityName="Bon" box="[398,656,567,590]" class="Bivalvia" family="Lasaeidae" genus="Rochfortia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galeommatida" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="steliata">
<emphasis box="[398,602,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Rochfortia steliata</emphasis>
Bon
</taxonomicName>
[sic!; = 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; P. Wilson" authorityName="Britton &amp; P. Wilson" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ehretiaceae" genus="Rochefortia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stellata">
<emphasis box="[756,972,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Rochefortia stellata</emphasis>
Britton &amp; P.Wilson
</taxonomicName>
] belonging to the family 
<taxonomicName box="[486,631,599,622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Boraginaceae</taxonomicName>
as host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zayas" authorityYear="1989" box="[813,955,599,622]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tortuguilla">
<emphasis box="[813,955,599,622]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">P. tortuguilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="SEKERKA L. &amp; WINDSOR D." pageId="35" pageNumber="310" pagination="669 - 677" refId="ref50531" refString="SEKERKA L. &amp; WINDSOR D. 2012: Two new species of Plagiometriona from Bolivia and Ecuador (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae: Cassidini). Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 62: 669 - 677." type="journal article" year="2012">SEKERKA &amp; WINDSOR (2012)</bibRefCitation>
summarized host plants of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[589,756,631,654]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,756,631,654]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and doubted that the record is valid assuming that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zayas" authorityYear="1989" box="[325,464,663,686]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tortuguilla">
<emphasis box="[325,464,663,686]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">P. tortuguilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
truly belong to this genus as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[770,937,663,686]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[770,937,663,686]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is exclusively associated with various 
<taxonomicName box="[366,489,695,718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
. The present transfer of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zayas" authorityYear="1989" box="[744,883,695,718]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tortuguilla">
<emphasis box="[744,883,695,718]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">P. tortuguilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is supported by the feeding association with 
<taxonomicName box="[375,520,727,750]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Boraginaceae</taxonomicName>
as recently the same plant family was reported as host of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Olivier, 1791) (SWIETOJANSKA &amp; WINDSOR 2008)" authorityName="SWIETOJANSKA &amp; WINDSOR" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[142,877,759,782]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Asteriza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[142,349,759,782]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="310">Asteriza flavicornis</emphasis>
(Olivier, 1791) (
<bibRefCitation author="SWIETOJANSKA J. &amp; WINDSOR D." box="[530,869,759,782]" pageId="35" pageNumber="310" pagination="641 - 665" refId="ref51716" refString="SWIETOJANSKA J. &amp; WINDSOR D. 2008: Immature stages of Asteriza flavicornis (Olivier) and Physonota alutacea Boheman (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 58: 641 - 665." type="journal article" year="2008">ŚWIĘTOJAŃSKA &amp; WINDSOR 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
